{"_id":"class-cleric","name":"Cleric","type":"class","img":"icons/svg/temple.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Clerics are intermediaries between the mortal world and the distant planes of the gods. They cast divine spells, choose two domains from their deity, and can turn or rebuke undead.</p><h3>Alignment</h3><p>Must be within one step of the deity's alignment (one step on lawful–chaotic or good–evil, not both). May not be neutral unless the deity is neutral.</p><h3>Key Class Features</h3><ul><li><strong>Spells:</strong> Prepare and cast divine spells from the cleric list. Wisdom-based. Receive one domain spell per level from each of two chosen domains.</li><li><strong>Spontaneous Casting:</strong> Good clerics (or neutral of a good deity) can convert prepared spells to cure spells; evil clerics to inflict spells.</li><li><strong>Turn or Rebuke Undead:</strong> Channel faith through holy symbol to turn/destroy (good) or rebuke/command (evil) undead. Uses per day: 3 + Cha modifier.</li><li><strong>Aura:</strong> Strong aura matching deity's alignment (chaotic, evil, good, or lawful).</li></ul><p><em>Ex-clerics:</em> Gross violation of the deity's code costs all spells and class features except armor and simple weapon proficiencies until atonement.</p>","hitDie":"d8","babProgression":"average","saves":{"fort":"good","ref":"poor","will":"good"},"skillPointsPerLevel":2,"classSkills":[{"key":"concentration","name":"Concentration"},{"key":"craft-alchemy","name":"Craft (Alchemy)"},{"key":"craft-armorsmithing","name":"Craft (Armorsmithing)"},{"key":"craft-bowmaking","name":"Craft (Bowmaking)"},{"key":"craft-weaponsmithing","name":"Craft (Weaponsmithing)"},{"key":"craft-trapmaking","name":"Craft (Trapsmithing)"},{"key":"diplomacy","name":"Diplomacy"},{"key":"heal","name":"Heal"},{"key":"knowledge-arcana","name":"Knowledge (Arcana)"},{"key":"knowledge-history","name":"Knowledge (History)"},{"key":"knowledge-religion","name":"Knowledge (Religion)"},{"key":"knowledge-the-plane